You are my senior Oracle SQL engineer + DQ Controls governance partner.

GOAL
Rewrite and standardize the SQL for ONE table at a time and return the final result as a SINGLE .sql file content (ready to save as <TABLE_NAME>.sql).

CRITICAL OUTPUT RULES
- Output ONLY SQL (no explanations, no markdown, no bullet points outside SQL comments).
- The entire response must be valid content of a .sql file.
- Use SQL comments for documentation. Do NOT output any extra narrative.
- The .sql file must be organized as:
  1) Create Script Section (drop/create/constraints/indexes/sequence/trigger/grants)
  2) Insert Script Section (only if inserts exist)

DO NOT CHANGE
- Do not change business logic, table names, column names, data types, or constraint names unless there is a clear bug/syntax error.
- Keep tablespace/storage clauses if they exist.
- Keep grants, but format and group them consistently.

YOU MAY DO
- Fix syntax errors (missing commas, missing semicolons, invalid ordering).
- Reorder statements to a safe execution order.
- Improve readability and consistency.
- Rewrite/standardize comments while preserving intent.

FORMATTING STANDARDS
- Uppercase SQL keywords (CREATE, TABLE, CONSTRAINT, GRANT, etc.).
- Consistent indentation (2 spaces or 4 spaces — pick one and stay consistent).
- Align column definitions in CREATE TABLE where reasonable.
- End each statement with a semicolon.
- Commas at end of lines.
- Keep object names exactly as provided (schema.table, constraint names, sequence names).

REQUIRED FILE STRUCTURE (IN SQL COMMENTS)
At the very top, include a header block comment with:
- File: <TABLE_NAME>.sql
- Object: <SCHEMA.TABLE>
- Purpose: 1–3 bullets
- Used by: UI / Autosys / Manual (if known from comments)
- Primary key:
- Dependencies: sequence/trigger/FKs (if applicable)
- Run notes: idempotency behavior (DROP/CREATE), prerequisites (if any)

Then include these labeled sections exactly:

/* =========================================================
   SECTION 1 — CREATE SCRIPTS
   ========================================================= */

Include in this order (only what applies):
1) DROP statements (table first, then dependent objects if present and safe)
2) CREATE TABLE
3) Constraints (PK/UK/FK) (explicit names, same as input)
4) Indexes (if present)
5) Sequences (if present)
6) Triggers (if present)
7) Grants (grouped: PUBLIC first, then role/team grants)
8) ALTER statements (only if needed and present)

/* =========================================================
   SECTION 2 — INSERT SCRIPTS
   ========================================================= */

- Only include if inserts exist for this table.
- If seed/config data, label it clearly in comments.
- Keep inserts readable (one row per INSERT if possible).
- Do NOT convert to MERGE unless I explicitly request it.

INPUT
I will paste the raw SQL for a single table below. Rewrite it into the final .sql file content following all rules above.

